      "scoring_520101": "Scoring Procedures and InterpretationThe Addiction Research Center Inventory (ARCI) answer sheet is in true-false format. In scoring all scales, one point is given for each response, which agrees with the scoring direction (Haertzen, 1974a). One point is given for each true response in items 1-21, 23-27, 31-40, 43-51, 55-65, and 70-81. One point is given for each false response in the reverse-scored items 22, 28-30, 41, 42, 52-54, and 66-69. The final score for each scale is the sum of the total true and reverse-scored false responses"
